verse_part: in the chief place of concourse,
But ye have set at nought
from them to whom it is due,
she shall bring thee to honour,
and those that seek me early
But he that sinneth against me
but he that is of a faithful
They that are of a froward
but he that is of a perverse
that which he took in hunting:
but [that which is] in the midst
and he that hath a perverse
and that which he hath given
I have made known to thee
That I might make thee know
to them that send unto thee?
them that are given to change:
than that thou shouldest be put lower
so much as is sufficient for thee,
but he that is a companion
but he that putteth his trust
and he shall give thee rest;
unto them that put their trust
and thou be found a liar.
unto him that is ready to perish,
unto those that be of heavy
